Staff-style weapons, a great one is with the staff held behind them in one hand, their other hand in front of them. It's usually open or in a claw-shape. Legs are spread apart, and the butt of the staff is almost touching the ground, continuing up almost parallel to the arm and emerging over the opposite shoulder to the arm using the staff.<br>
Scythe. Hmm, tricky. You could go for the staff stance, but as most scythes have a handle for the other hand, you could go for: Feet about shoulder-width apart, right hand on the main haft. Left hand on the second handle. The scythe is held at about a 45 degree angle in front of the body.<br>
If by a double edge you mean like a staff but with a blade on either end, the staff stance is usually good enough.<br>
I'd draw them for you, but I'm a writer, rather than an artist.<br>
